<p>&#8216;Victims of domestic abuse can be spared from being cross-examined by their alleged attackers in family and civil courts under measures coming into force today (21 July 2022).&#8217;</p>
<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/domestic-abusers-barred-from-cross-examining-victims-in-family-and-civil-courts">Full Story</a></p><p> Ministry of Justice, 21st July 2022</p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk">www.gov.uk</a></p>